# ENDOS Roadmap

## Sprint 1 – Foundation

Goal: Establish ENDOS as a stable public repository and GitHub Pages platform.

Deliverables:

- GitHub Pages website
- Professional repository structure
- README and documentation baseline
- Release notes and changelog
- Initial architecture baseline

## Sprint 2 – Executive Mission Control

Goal: Turn the landing page into an operational executive workspace.

Planned modules:

- Today's Mission
- Current Sprint
- Top Priorities
- Open Gaps
- Decision Focus
- Architecture Status
- Research Watch
- Pilot Readiness

## Sprint 3 – Architecture Explorer

Goal: Provide a structured, navigable view of ENDOS architecture.

Planned modules:

- Layer map
- Engine map
- Object model
- Decision flow
- Method orchestration view

## Sprint 4 – Knowledge Repository Browser

Goal: Make Knowledge Objects, Patent Objects and Architecture Decisions searchable and understandable.

Planned modules:

- Object cards
- Category filters
- Evidence status
- Gap indicators
- Object lifecycle

## Sprint 5 – Validation Center

Goal: Build evidence through historical replay and pilot cases.

Candidate replay cases:

- Nokia
- Kodak
- Leoni
- Signa
- Siemens Energy
- Continental
- ZF
- Microsoft

## Sprint 6 – Patent Intelligence

Goal: Structure patent families, claims, novelty areas and search evidence.

## Sprint 7 – Pilot Evidence Management

Goal: Prepare structured pilots, quick findings and ROI evidence.

## Sprint 8 – Enterprise Knowledge Graph

Goal: Connect objects, signals, methods, decisions, interventions and outcomes.
